#X text 23 7 distance-sensor-02.pd | Paul V. Miller \, February 2026 | Duquesne University This patch listens for OSC messages over UDP on a local WiFi network \, and routes them to the correct student subpatch. Each transmitter sends a unique boxID. Multiple devices can be used simultaneously in an ensemble performance. We use objects in the virtual sound library which can be found at: https://virtual-sound.com/pure-data-electronic-music-and-sound-design-volume-1-support/ A Python script on a Raspberry Pi Pico W running Micropython interfaces with the hardware \, formats the OSC message \, and sends it out. This can be downloaded from my GitHub site., f 118;
